beau &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; is a 1924 american silent film historical drama starring john barrymore and mary astor . the film was directed by harry beaumont and based upon clyde fitch 's 1890 play , which had been performed by richard mansfield , and depicts the life of the british regency dandy beau &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; . several years after barrymore 's death , his daughter diana barrymore was shown a special screening of this film as she had never seen her father in any of his silent films . in 1952 , the film entered the public domain in the united states due to the failure of warner bros. to renew the copyright in the 28th year after registration .